Introduction
============

Compilation Notes for Sorcery on Linux. Updated 11th July 2026.

My Development Environment is:

- Ubuntu 26.04 LTS
- GCC 14.2+ (though this may change to GCC15 minimum at some point)
- CMake 3.22+

Current C++ standard used is C++23.

Git Notes
=========

IMPORTANT! You'll need git lfs enabled to get the image files in the gfx
directory due to their size, else you will not get any images. 

Please note as of 4th July 2026, I have replaced the master branch with the 
sdl/imgui branch and have archived the older SFML-based version of the code. 
That branch is no longer updated, and will also be archived in the near future.


VSCode Notes
============

- VSCode 1.127
- C/C++ extension 1.29.3 (note that 1.32.2 currently breaks debugging in VSCode)
- CMake Tools extension 1.23.52

Additional Tools

I also use bear to produce compile-commands.json for Intelliense plugins (to 
install near use apt install bear, then use it by calling
bear -- make -j <number of your cores>)


Code Formatting
===============

Clang-tidy support via the format file in /.clang-format.

Dependencies
============

To summarise:

SDL2, OpenGL, jsoncpp, SQLite3, PkgConfig, FreeType, glm, FFmpeg, pthreads

